# Northside Intelligence — Cursor Rules

## UI capitalization

Apply Title Case to all button labels, CTAs, nav actions, and short UI chrome (badges, tabs, pill filters) unless the control is intentionally compact (then ALL CAPS is acceptable).

Examples:
- Get Started
- Sign In / Sign Up / Sign Out
- Create Account
- Open Tool
- Explore Tools
- Verify & Continue

Use normal sentence capitalization only for paragraph-style body copy, descriptions, and long-form content — not for buttons, headings, or bold title text unless explicitly requested otherwise.

Do not use arrow suffixes on button text (e.g. prefer "Open Dashboard" over "Open dashboard →").

## Sector 3 Tool Naming Rules

When generating new Sector 3 tool names (via generate-tool edge function or any prompt):

REQUIREMENTS:
- Max 2 words
- Marketable standalone — could exist without "NI" surrounding it
- Punchy, memorable, benefit-implied
- No generic AI words: SmartX, AIBot, IntelliX, AutoX, etc.
- Pass the "would someone search for this?" test

GOOD EXAMPLES: ReplyFlow, GrantBot, Outreach HQ, Content Creator Rx, Ad Sensei,
               PitchDeck, InvoiceAce, LeadSnap, CloseKit, ToneCheck

BAD EXAMPLES: AIReply, SmartOutreach, IntelliContent, AutoAds, NI Outreach Tool
